                <h1>Emotional Trigger Snapshot </h1>
                <p>For each emotion you can select a value between 0 and 10.</p>
                <p> You do not have to select a value for all of them if you do not wish to do so.</p>
                <p> An optional trigger may be choosen from the list below also. </p>
                <p> You can choose no trigger for now and make changes at a later date should you wish</p>

                <form method="post" action="/new" class="centered-form">
                    <div>
                        <label class="date-input">Date and Time of Entry: </label>
                        <input type="datetime-local" id="datetime-input" name="snapshot_date">
                    </div>

                    <p class="special">ENJOYMENT</p>
                    <div class="input-group number-input">
                        <input type="number" min="0" max="10" value="0" class="form-control" name="enjoyment">
                        <div class="input-group-append">
                        </div>
                    </div>

                    <p class="special">SURPRISE</p>
                    <div class="input-group number-input">
                        <input type="number" min="0" max="10" value="0" class="form-control" name="surprise">
                        <div class="input-group-append">
                        </div>
                    </div>

                    <p class="special">CONTEMPT</p>
                    <div class="input-group number-input">
                        <input type="number" min="0" max="10" value="0" class="form-control" name="contempt">
                        <div class="input-group-append">
                        </div>
                    </div>

                    <p class="special">SADNESS</p>
                    <div class="input-group number-input">
                        <input type="number" min="0" max="10" value="0" class="form-control" name="sadness">
                        <div class="input-group-append">
                        </div>
                    </div>

                    <p class="special">FEAR</p>
                    <div class="input-group number-input">
                        <input type="number" min="0" max="10" value="0" class="form-control" name="fear">
                        <div class="input-group-append">
                        </div>
                    </div>

                    <p class="special">DISGUST</p>
                    <div class="input-group number-input">
                        <input type="number" min="0" max="10" value="0" class="form-control" name="disgust">
                        <div class="input-group-append">
                        </div>
                    </div>

                    <p class="special">ANGER</p>
                    <div class="input-group number-input">
                        <input type="number" min="0" max="10" value="0" class="form-control" name="anger">
                        <div class="input-group-append">
                        </div>
                    </div>


                    <p class="special">
                        <label for="trigger-input"> Which of the following triggers do you think contributed to
                            this?</label>
                    </p>

                    <div id="dropdown">
                        <select name="trigger_ID" id="trigger-input">
                            <option value="Family">Family</option>
                            <option value="Friends">Friends</option>
                            <option value="Relationship">Relationship</option>
                            <option value="Health">Health</option>
                            <option value="Finances">Finances</option>
                            <option value="Work">Work</option>
                            <option value="Current Environment">Current Environment</option>
                            <option value="Diet">Diet</option>
                            <option value="A Recent Event">A Recent Event</option>
                            <option value="Unknown">Unknown</option>
                            <option value="No Trigger">no trigger</option>
                        </select>
                    </div>

                    <div>
                        <input type="submit" value="submit" class="green-button">
                    </div>

